The group of fifteen on aiming at schism
“On the invitation day it may happen that five or more resident monks have gathered in a certain monastery.
that there are other resident monks who haven’t arrived.
They think, ʻMay they get lost! May they disappear! Who needs them?’
And aiming at schism, they do the invitation procedure.
During the procedure a greater number of resident monks arrive.
In such a case those monks should do the invitation procedure once more.
And there’s a serious offense for those who already have invited.
On the invitation day it may happen that five or more resident monks have gathered in a certain monastery.
that there are other resident monks who haven’t arrived.
They think, ʻMay they get lost! May they disappear! Who needs them?’
And aiming at schism, they do the invitation procedure.
During the procedure an equal number of resident monks arrive.
In such a case the invitations of those who already have invited are valid, but the others should invite.
And there’s a serious offense for those who already have invited.
