legitimately but with an incomplete assembly. …
in a legitimate-like way and with an incomplete assembly. …
in a legitimate-like way but unanimous. …”
The permutation series is to be expanded.
Discussion of the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view
“It may be that a monk doesn’t wish to give up a bad view.
The monks consider,
‘This monk doesn’t wish to give up a bad view.
Well then, let’s do a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view against him.’
They do a procedure of ejection against him—
illegitimately and with an incomplete assembly.
He then goes to another monastery.
There too the monks consider,
‘The Sangha did a legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view against this monk—illegitimately and with an incomplete assembly.
